   BOISE, Idaho -- Morrison Knudsen Corp. and a joint-venture
associate said they have received a $40 million contract to
build a 57-mile underwater natural gas pipeline in British
Columbia.
   Morrison Knudsen's Vancouver-based unit, Northern
Construction Co., and Stena Offshore Ltd., of Aberdeen,
Scotland, will build the pipeline, which will run from the
British Columbia mainland to Vancouver Island. Work will
start immediately and be completed by December.
