   MILPITAS, Calif. -- LSI Logic Corp. said its Headland
Technology affiliate has signed an agreement valued at as
much as $20 million to supply Hewlett-Packard (Canada) Ltd.
with advanced video graphics boards for use in
Hewlett-Packard's Vectra personal computers.
   LSI Logic Corp of Canada Inc. will manufacture the boards
in Canada. The high-performance graphic cards reduce wait
times to "virtually zero," the company said.
