<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- William J. Nasgovitz, president of Heartland
Advisors Inc., a Milwaukee investment advisory firm, said he
holds a 5.2% stake in Rexworks Inc.'s common stock for
investment purposes.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
Mr. Nasgovitz said he holds 93,552 shares, including 39,000
shares purchased between May 4 and May 21 for $3.50 to $3.73
a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Rexworks, based in Milwaukee, makes concrete mixer
equipment.
