   Marketing Brief -- Time Warner Inc.:
   Firm Completes Acquisition
   Of Lane for $225 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
06/04/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7
</SO>
<CO>
   TWX
</CO>
<IN>
MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Time Warner Inc. said it completed the acquisition of Lane
Publishing Co. for $225 million.
   Lane Publishing, Menlo Park, Calif., publishes Sunset, the
Magazine of Western Living, and Sunset Books, and produces
Sunset Films. The acquisition makes media and entertainment
giant Time Warner the nation's largest publisher of regional
magazines.
</LP>
