<LP>
   DALLAS -- Recognition Equipment Inc. said it delayed a
planned tender offer for $15 million to $20 million of its
stock for up to six more months while it works on improving
its business and continues to try to sell assets.
   The maker of document-processing equipment initially
agreed to purchase its stock when Prospect Group Inc., a New
York leveraged buy-out concern, made a $15 million loan to
the company. However, Prospect later agreed to let
Recognition use the funds for short-term working capital for
as long as four months after it made the loan in February.
</LP>
