   Recognition said its board moved to further amend the
agreement with Prospect after considering the capital needs
associated with its plans to focus on its imaging equipment
and because planned asset sales are moving more slowly than
expected. It also cited pending settlement discussions with
the U.S. Federal Reserve Banks over a contract dispute
involving currency-processing systems.
   The company said that delaying the tender offer until as
late as the end of November will allow it to look at its
results for the year ending Oct. 31. A spokeswoman said the
decision isn't the result of a liquidity problem, saying the
company had approximately $48 million in cash and equivalents
at April 30.
