   BOSTON -- Bank of New England Corp. said it completed the
sale of its BancNewEngland Leasing Group operations to Bank
of Tokyo Ltd.
   The sale, approved by the Federal Reserve May 21, includes
about $500 million in assets, the bank said. Bank of Tokyo
will assume the group's 250 employees in a new subsidiary,
BOT Financial Corp., based in Boston.
